Requirements:
To be considered for admission to the Executive MBA program, candidates must fulfill the following requirements:

*   Have a minimum of six to eight years of work experience with an increasing level of responsibility (management experience is strongly preferred)
*   Hold a baccalaureate degree from an accredited institution

A completed graduate application.
A master’s degree in a business or non-business field or a bachelor’s degree with a very high GPA from an accredited institution. An MBA or a specialized business master’s degree is preferred.
Official transcripts (in English) of all previously completed undergraduate and graduate course work.
A minimum GPA of 3.3 (or equivalent).
A competitive GMAT or GRE score, taken within five years of applying. GMAT/GRE waivers are considered on a case-by-case basis. To be considered, please submit a GMAT/GRE waiver request.

To be considered for admission to the data science MS program, candidates must fulfill the following requirements:

Hold a baccalaureate degree (or equivalent) from an accredited university or college in a quantitatively-based field, including mathematics, statistics, computer science, engineering, information science, or other related scientific discipline.
A recommended minimum cumulative GPA of 3.0 (or equivalent).

To be considered for admission to the Master of Science Program in Secondary Education of Students Who Are Deaf or Hard of Hearing (MSSE), candidates must fulfill the following requirements:
- Complete an online application.
- Hold a baccalaureate degree from an accredited college or university.
- Have a minimum cumulative GPA of 3.0 (on a 4.0 scale). Applicants with a GPA lower than 3.0 may be considered for admission based on other indicators of success, including a successful interview with program faculty.
- Provide official transcripts (in English) of all previously completed undergraduate and graduate course work.
- Provide two letters of recommendation. It is strongly recommended that at least one of these be from a former professor or instructor.
- A current resume.
- A two- to three-page, typed, double-spaced statement of purpose that discusses the following:
  - Your reason for choosing teaching as a profession
  - How prior work, volunteer and/or life experiences have prepared you for a career in teaching
  - Your philosophy of education for deaf and hard-of-hearing students
- Participate in a personal interview (in person or by videophone/videoconference).
- Applicants must demonstrate a minimum level of sign language proficiency equivalent to the successful completion of ASL IV.

Requirements:
To be considered for admission to the Mechanical Engineering MS program, candidates must fulfill the following requirements:

* Complete a graduate application.
* Hold a baccalaureate degree (or equivalent) from an accredited university or college in an engineering discipline. Applicants with degrees in math, physics, or other technical disciplines may be admitted but may be required to complete undergraduate bridge courses before matriculating into the graduate program.
* Have a minimum cumulative GPA of 3.0 (or equivalent). Applicants with a GPA lower than 3.0 may be admitted on a conditional basis. These candidates must achieve a GPA of 3.0 in their first nine credit hours of graduate course work to continue in the program.
* Submit official transcripts (in English) from all previously completed undergraduate and graduate course work.
* Submit a statement of purpose (approximately 500 words).
* Submit a current resume or curriculum vitae.
* Submit two letters of recommendation from academic or professional sources.
* Submit GRE scores. The GRE is required. To be competitive, recommended scores are verbal 151, quantitative 159, and analytical writing 3.5. (GRE requirement is waived for applicants who have a degree from an ABET-accredited U.S. institution or a school on our international top university list.
